- "shining stars" refers to stocks with a CAGR greater than the average CAGR of their sector;
- "how bright do they shine" refers to the CAGR returns of these stocks;
- CAGR (Compound Annual Growth Rate) is a measure of the mean annual growth rate of an investment over a specified time period.

- "Star in the financial sky" refers to a stock;
- "Shines the brightest in terms of growth" refers to the highest Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR);
